        <h3>Open-core, extensible design</h3>
        <p>
          The core compiler and language are MIT-licensed. Enterprises can extend MIND with private backends, passes, and runtimes without forking the language.
        </p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>Open-source core for community innovation</li>
          <li>Pluggable executors for custom hardware</li>
          <li>FFI hooks for C/C++ and Python interoperability</li>
        </ul>
